Sting usually made his television appearances on
late night television.  Here is a samplng of morning
programs that reinforce that very wise decision.

1. Good Morning America (ABC)
Pt.1 12-10-87
Host: Joan Lunden
Correspondent: Jeff Greenfield

Interview covering Sting's humanitarian efforts
with behind the scenes footage from his concert 
in Porto Allegre, Brazil.

2. Good Morning America (ABC)
Pt.2 12-11-87

Jeff Greenfield's interview continued.

3. The Today Show (NBC)
Host: Bryant Gumbel

Bryant interviews Sting in the NBC Today Show
studios on the release date of "Ten Summoner's Tales".

4. "Live with Regis and Kathie Lee" 
3-18-96
Hosts: Regis Philbin, Kathie Lee Gifford

This one is outrageous...Sting is ambushed by the 
morning talk show cheese factor.  I think he had
no idea what he was getting into, and seems a bit
annoyed when Regis accidentally spits on him.

5. "The Rosie O'Donnell Show"
3-4-97
Host: Rosie O'Donnell

Sting's wife Trudy Styler joins him on this one
to discuss the premiere of their film -
"Gentlemen Don't Eat Poets", which was about to 
open in Greenwich Village.  In typical fashion,
Rosie has not done a great job with researching her 
guests, but thankfully avoids the rock bottom depths of
the Regis and Kathie Lee appearance a year earlier
